## REST API Conceptual Diagram

```
+-------+           +-----------+           +-----------+           +-----------+
|       |  Request  |           |  Process  |           |  Fetch /  |           |
|       |  -------> |           |  -------> |           |  Modify   |           |
|       |           |           |           |           |  -------> |           |
|       | <-------  |           | <-------  |           |           |           |
|       | Response  |           |  Return   |           |           |           |
+-------+           +-----------+           +-----------+           +-----------+
  Client              Web Server              API Server               Database
```

---

## Components Explained

### Client

The requester of the service.

- Web browser
- Mobile application
- Another backend system

### Web Server

- Receives HTTP/HTTPS requests
- Performs routing
- Handles load balancing
- Forwards requests to the API server

### API Server

- Core business logic
- Processes requests
- Interacts with the database
- Returns structured responses (usually JSON)

### Database
